Encoded from the Spanish Divisa blu-ray release.

&quot;Restoration by the BFI National Archive in association with ITV Studios Global Entertainment and Park Circus Films&quot;

This 2012 restoration runs to 105 minutes long. That's over 20 minutes longer than previous DVD releases.
There is no additional footage, instead the blu-ray plays at 24 fps with a repeat every 6 frames to create the effect of 20 fps playback. Effectively slowing the speed of this oldie to a modern, life-like motion instead of the hastened pace of the original.
There is room for much debate on the pros and cons of restoring the silents to blu-ray.

** For this encode the extra frames were removed creating a 20 fps rip with no dupe frames.

